---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Downloads" description="Install BridgeAIChat app and agent releases.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Downloads</div>
    <h1>Install through Homebrew, fall back to GitHub Releases.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The public distribution model is simple: GitHub Releases remain the source of truth for binaries, and the
      BridgeAIChat Homebrew tap turns those release assets into a clean install path for macOS and Linuxbrew users.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">bridge-app</div>
      <h2>Gateway + hosted UI</h2>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-app
bridge-gateway</pre>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/bridge-ai-chat/bridge-app/releases">Browse GitHub Releases</a></p>
      <div class="note"><strong>Fallback:</strong> download the matching archive and run <code>bash install-app.sh</code>.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">bridge-agent</div>
      <h2>Remote device runtime</h2>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-agent
bash "$(brew --prefix)/share/bridge-agent/install-agent.sh"</pre>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/bridge-ai-chat/bridge-agent/releases">Browse GitHub Releases</a></p>
      <div class="note"><strong>Fallback:</strong> download the matching archive and run <code>bash install-agent.sh</code>.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Compatibility</div>
      <h2>Version matrix</h2>
      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>App</th>
              <th>Agent</th>
              <th>Tested setups</th>
              <th>Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>v0.1.0-beta.1</td>
              <td>v0.1.0-beta.1</td>
              <td>macOS host + macOS agent, macOS host + Linux VPS agent, macOS host + Raspberry Pi/Linux ARM agent</td>
              <td>Codex-first happy path. Claude supported with device quota and login caveats.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
